  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      An increase in dietary protein intake has been shown to blunt the increase in intrahepatic
      fat induced by high fat feeding in healthy individuals. The purpose of this study is to
      determine if a protein supplementation decreases intrahepatic fat in obese patients with
      non-alcoholic fatty liver disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      12 obese patients will be be treated with a dietary whey protein supplementation over 4
      weeks. Their intrahepatic fat content, glucose tolerance, and body weight will be evaluated
      before and after 4 weeks of supplementation.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
